cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY 

The paper deals with the discovery of similar Twitter accounts based on the content they disseminate, which involves the use of Twitter entities such as mentions, replies, hashtags, photos, and URLs. This falls under the domain of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), as the methodology involves semantic representation protocols and related technologies. Additionally, the paper also describes an ontological schema for semantification, which could be related to Semantic Web (cs.SI) and Software Engineering (cs.SD). Finally, the use of Twitter entities and their analysis could also be relevant to Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
